"Today, I rise to say to my constituents and my colleagues that we can pass meaningful criminal justice reform” @CoryBooker
"African Americans are 21% more likely to receive mandatory minimum sentence than whites facing similar charges.” @CoryBooker

"The U.S. incarceration rate is 5 to 10 times that of many Western European countries” @CoryBooker
"From 1990 to 2005, a new prison opened every ten days in the United States” @CoryBooker

"This critical legislation has support of dozens of civil rights groups, faith groups, law enforcement and prosecutor groups" @CoryBooker

"What these laws have done is cause an 800 percent increase in our federal prison population over the last 30 years.” @CoryBooker
"In 2015, the federal government spent over $2.3 billion warehousing people who received a mandatory minimum at sentencing.” @CoryBooker
“This amendment, instead of focusing on the root causes of the opioid problem, calls for increased mandatory minimum sentencing” @CoryBooker
"Over the past 10 years, we have lost over 1500 people under the age of 30 to heroin overdoses in New Jersey alone” ~ @CoryBooker
